## Commands

```bash
npm run dev       # Start development server
npm run build     # Build for production
npm run test      # Run tests
npm run lint      # Lint code
{{#if has_e2e}}
npm run e2e       # Run E2E tests
{{/if}}
```

## Performance

- MUST use lazy loading for routes and heavy components
- MUST optimize images (WebP format, responsive sizes)
- MUST implement proper caching strategies
- Target Lighthouse score: > 90 for all metrics

## Accessibility

- MUST include descriptive alt text on all images
- MUST use semantic HTML elements (header, nav, main, footer)
- MUST support keyboard navigation
- MUST maintain color contrast ratio >= 4.5:1
- MUST test with screen readers

## State Management

- Prefer server state (React Query/SWR) over client state
- Use local state for UI-only concerns
- Avoid prop drilling - use context sparingly

## Styling

{{#if tailwind}}
- Use Tailwind utility classes
- Extract repeated patterns to components
- Use design tokens for consistency
{{else}}
- Use CSS Modules or styled-components
- Follow BEM naming if using plain CSS
- Keep styles co-located with components
{{/if}}
